items.title: Cubs erupt for 7-run 6th to turn tables on Cards
items.summary: After losing their starting pitcher and catcher to ejections in the fifth inning, the Cubs rallied with a seven-run sixth inning on Friday afternoon to open an 8-2 lead against the Cardinals in a showdown of National League Central rivals.
items.content: After losing their starting pitcher and catcher to ejections in the fifth inning, the Cubs rallied with a seven-run sixth inning on Friday afternoon to open an 8-2 lead against the Cardinals in a showdown of National League Central rivals.

items.title: Wong exits with lower back tightness
items.summary: A half-inning after scoring from second on Carlos Martinez's two-out, fifth-inning single, Kolten Wong was pulled from Friday afternoon's series opener vs. the Cubs at Wrigley Field due to lower back tightness. Greg Garcia replaced Wong at second base.

items.title: MLB: Tigers didn't intentionally hit umpire
items.summary: Major League Baseball is reviewing the circumstances surrounding the pitch from Tigers right-hander Buck Farmer that hit home-plate umpire Quinn Wolcott in the shoulder after catcher James McCann and manager Brad Ausmus were ejected from Wednesday's 5-3 loss to the Indians.
